Value.Text: Lily, I’ve been meaning to talk about this. Me and Astrid had a chat, and…
Astrid? Did she say anything about me?
No, that’s confidential.
Go on.
*I want to know what Astrid talked about with this swine…*
We really think you shouldn’t joke about killing people so much.
Me and Astrid know that you’re joking, but especially since you’re carrying that sword around, other people might not understand your… sense of humour… as well as we do.
I’m just looking out for you, eh?
Dialogue text.
Lilith, the Queen of Darkness.
Lily Brown! How nice to see you!
Pardon?
Lilith. The Queen. Of Darkness.

Darkness? Isn’t that rather glum? 
To me, you look more like Lilith, the Queen of…
Don’t.
Suit yourself.
Anyway, I was just about to collect Snuffles. We’re going to the park, aren’t we, Snuffie?
Would you like to join us, … Lilith?
Dialogue text.

Choices.Text: I’d rather die. Or you should.

Value.Text: Karl, I think we both know how this is going to end.
It’s a pity, really, you’re sweet and I would have liked to keep you around… pfft… pffffff –
HAHAHAHAHAHA!
I can’t even say it with a straight face!

Anyway…
You give me no choice but to kill…

Did you say grill?
Never mind the dog park, there is always time for some barbeque!
HONEY DO YOU WANT ANYTHING?

No, sweetheart! We just had barbeque this morning! 
Ask Lily if she’s hungry!
Lily, want anything? I make scrumptious steak.
Dialogue text.

No! I want to… 
(This is my chance to hurt him mentally, before going for the physical damage.)
You are so kind! Thank you!
How thick can he get?

These kinds of people shouldn’t be allowed to live and reproduce…
Especially with someone like…
Better I don’t think about that.
Anyway, it seems I’ll have to do the world a favour…
Do take her out. I’ll walk the dog. See what happens.

She doesn’t even like you. 
What reason would she have to like you?
Being her husband?
I liked it so I put a ri…
Don't.
*Humming Single Ladies*
I can’t allow this to continue…

Killing him will be natural selection.
To make sure no genes that annoying pass to the next generation.
How can you tell it’s in quotation marks?
Spider sense.
Oh my Satan…
Okay. But the point is. He doesn’t like you.

He doesn’t?
Let’s test it, champ.
We’ll both call him. Let’s see which one he picks.
Okay.
Hellhound!
Snuffles!
That's cheating.
How is it cheating?

It just is! And now you will die!
I will fight you!
Why did you say it in quotation marks?
I want you to know that “your” dog doesn’t even like you.
I’ve always wanted us to be friends.
Don’t speak over me.

Anyway, me and Astrid had a chat. You know, woman to woman.
Has she not told you?
Told me what?
What?
Astrid? Is this true?
Is what true?
That you don’t like my barbeque…?
Is it?

...
I mean...
I can’t believe this!

I just didn’t want to say anything!
You seem so into it, and you seem so happy while doing it, so…

She doesn’t actually enjoy your barbeque.
She just says she does to not hurt your feelings.
…you don’t like my steaks?
I don’t eat meat!
I thought you liked them so much that you still eat them when I make them.
Karl, älskling…

No, don’t “älskling” your way out of this!
We are still cuddling later when we watch the ten o’clock news but just know that I am very, very upset!
Good!
What?
And now I will fight you!
Well, that is good.
What?
I want to tell you something honest. I feel like a friend would tell you.
Yes. The fight is good. Because I have a licence…
DON’T SAY IT –
…TO GRILL!

Please never say that again about him.
He's my hound.
But if you want to walk him sometimes, I won’t be saying no to having a day off! Ha ha!
Romantic night out with min älskling! Don’t remember the last time me and Astrid had the time.
As much as Snuffles loves you, neighbour, he has my name in his collar.
What is he called then? Snuftelius, the Guard of the Abyss?
Dialogue text.
I will kill you.
You are absolutely right. I will stop joking about it.
Except the cool ones such as Astrid and myself! Hahaha!

This cannot continue…
This is why he made it to the list… I’m ending this now…
I’m sure they’re funny among the other kids, but adults don’t always have such a good humour.
